        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="1199" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1199">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <persName corresp="#p_THS1">Truman</persName> Papers</note>
                <head>No. 1199<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">President <persName corresp="#p_THS1" type="from">Truman</persName> to Prime Minister <persName corresp="#p_CWS1" type="to">Churchill</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Babelsberg</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-23">23 July
                            1945</date>.<note n="1" xml:id="d1199fn1">The date appears as a
                            manuscript addition, in brackets, on the source copy.</note>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Memorandum for the Prime Minister</hi>
                </p>
                <p>In 1942 when the munitions resources of the United States and the United Kingdom
                    were insufficient to meet the requirements of the United Nations forces you and
                    President <persName corresp="#p_RFD1">Roosevelt</persName> agreed to pool our
                    munitions resources and to create Munitions Assignments Boards in London and
                    Washington to assign finished <gloss target="#t_War1">war</gloss> material to
                    the several United Nations in accordance with strategic need.</p>
                <p>Since the munitions resources of the United States and the United Kingdom are now
                    generally more than sufficient to insure the success of combined strategy, I
                    consider that the Munitions Assignments Board, Washington, no longer serves a
                    useful purpose. I therefore propose to abolish this Board and would appreciate
                    your concurrence in this action.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_THS1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Harry</hi> S. <hi rend="smallcaps">Truman</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
